textBody:
The discovery of the 118 chemical elements known to exist today is presented here in chronological order. The elements are listed generally in the order in which each was first defined as the pure element, as the exact date of discovery of most elements cannot be accurately defined. There are plans to synthesise more elements.

Given is each element's name, atomic number, year of first report, name of the discoverer, and some notes related to the discovery.
